Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.15,0:01:38.20,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Act 9\NSerious Bomber"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, our lord's carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.75,0:01:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back safely!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.92,0:01:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Elf. Please look, princess, it's Elf!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.39,0:02:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the heck do you have\Nto come with me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.39,0:02:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, princess, it's not fair for\Nyou to have them all to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.89,0:02:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Share with us, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.35,0:02:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--By the way, princess...\N--Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.94,0:02:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Drifters' next target\Nwill probably be Gadolka.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.28,0:02:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll likely to attempt\Nto free the Dwarves there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.70,0:02:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, their security is very tight\Nas it is the largest armory in Orte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.96,0:02:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.29,0:02:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no idea what\Nthe Drifters are capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.67,0:02:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Gadolka falls, the end of\Nthis country will be inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.87,0:03:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are all these weapons also\Ngoing to the western front?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.62,0:03:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We were told by headquarters\Nthe naval transport unit was destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.71,0:03:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,putting us in dire need of weapons and armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.98,0:03:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, they ordered us to\Nincrease the production quota.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.46,0:03:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we need to get the Dwarves\Nto ramp up production.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.30,0:03:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.81,0:03:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...increasing the workload\Nany further is just abuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.18,0:03:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will drop dead one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.37,0:03:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite a few of them have\Nalready been worked to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.82,0:03:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What the...?!\N--What the hell is happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.53,0:03:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the mine collapse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.79,0:03:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The soil taken from the toilet's subfloor,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.12,0:03:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the sulfur from Boobienu, and charcoal...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.33,0:03:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the perfect combination for...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.75,0:03:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...black powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.88,0:04:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.98,0:04:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hell is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.06,0:04:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The primary effect of gunpowder is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.35,0:04:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...not the flames that char the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.80,0:04:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor the shrapnel that tears through flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're charging forward. Raise the battle cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.95,0:04:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy is terrified. Get them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.15,0:04:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the sound and light, \Nthe shock and awe...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...utter terror...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.42,0:04:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cannons, fire arrows, and firearms\Nall have the same effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.76,0:04:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Shimazu clan controls Tanegashima,\Nthe birthplace of Japan's first firearm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.23,0:04:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no surprise that Toyo knows\Nhow best to put them to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rush them down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.07,0:05:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy! It's an enemy attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the Elves?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.82,0:05:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a revolt?! Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.62,0:05:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn demihumans!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.28,0:05:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.29,0:05:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.05,0:05:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What a terrible concoction...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had no clue that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.68,0:05:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was having us create such \Na terrible powder all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.06,0:05:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mix it carefully, or else\Nwe all may die. Cautiously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.12,0:05:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down. It's all right.\NYou Elves are all incredibly dexterous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's rain arrows down upon them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.98,0:05:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These explosive arrows aren't bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.34,0:05:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they'd work about \Nthe same as fire arrows,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.95,0:05:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but in the hands of Yoichi and the Elves,\Nthey became devastating weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I wasn't expecting\Nthem to burn this well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We could have taken so many supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.58,0:05:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well, it's too bad. Such a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.13,0:06:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.34,0:06:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.59,0:06:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shout! Shout! Bring them to their knees!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to blow! The \Nfire is rapidly spreading!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.84,0:06:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run! They have us surrounded!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.64,0:06:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will kill us all! Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.35,0:06:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.85,0:06:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hell is happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.85,0:06:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give them the chance to rally!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.52,0:06:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this looks bad. Let's get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.66,0:06:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the castle town! Charge forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.08,0:06:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go invade the town!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.31,0:06:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ground you step on\Nis Orte's largest armory,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.23,0:07:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and this land is protected by us,\Nthe Armored Guards Corps of Orte!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall not give in to you rebels.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.36,0:07:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy armor, heavy swords, heavy spears...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...no arrows, no bow, and no horses...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.18,0:07:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Withdraw!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.96,0:07:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Running?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.36,0:07:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't let you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.23,0:07:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olminu... I wonder if she is doing all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.67,0:07:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be no problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those guys from the deserted castle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.47,0:07:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,should be able to put Olminu's \Npowers to full effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.72,0:07:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Olminu of Stone Coffins."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.52,0:07:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her casting of the "Stone Wall Spell" is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.23,0:07:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...unmatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.24,0:07:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, she is probably the\Nmost talented one among you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:07:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...especially in the chest area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.54,0:08:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you sound like a dirty old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.37,0:08:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming from someone who is\Nactually 83 years old, that fits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.50,0:08:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.25,0:08:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toss them over!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.63,0:08:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy is falling apart.\NPerfect opportunity!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.18,0:08:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worth its weight in gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.47,0:08:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our heavy infantry was destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it... What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.14,0:08:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gate! Close the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Close the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.65,0:08:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing he used the\N"Stone Walls" in that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.07,0:08:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Toyohisa! As might be\Nexpected... that was a dirty trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The spell was supposed to be for defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.83,0:08:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, he used it to annihilate the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.66,0:08:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is as if he were born to\Ntake on the battlefield himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.62,0:08:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, they closed the castle gate.\NThat could be problematic...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.25,0:08:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:08:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa, are those raspberries good?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.68,0:08:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:08:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did he even come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.68,0:09:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are we supposed to deal with\Nthis stupid southern barbarian?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.80,0:09:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Messenger! Messenger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.82,0:09:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to send a message to Olminu!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.33,0:09:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.20,0:09:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa... you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want more raspberries! I want more!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no more left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't give me more raspberries,\NCarthage will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.46,0:09:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.42,0:09:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I just talk into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this sphere?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olminu said it would work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.14,0:09:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in, Boobies! Come in!\NCan you hear me, Boobienu?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.94,0:09:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.56,0:09:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember my name, you jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.56,0:09:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't give a damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.32,0:09:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should still have\Nthe charms for the "Stone Walls," right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.61,0:09:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do as I tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:09:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can make things work with\Nyour charms and Yoichi's archery!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.28,0:10:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gate is closing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.08,0:10:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell just exploded...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.46,0:10:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know. I lit the signal fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.92,0:10:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll probably take half a day for\Nreinforcements to arrive, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's almost impossible for them to\Nbesiege the castle with the gate closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.55,0:10:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will crash them against our walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.93,0:10:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The troops in the areas outside\Nthe walls are falling apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.77,0:10:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very few soldiers are left!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.10,0:10:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn demihumans!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When reinforcements arrive,\Nwe'll attack those idiots from both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.66,0:10:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are stairs on the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.74,0:10:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobu! It's amazing! Nobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.08,0:10:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, the "Stone Walls" are great,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.58,0:10:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they cannot be better than this sphere\Nby any stretch of the imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no need of messengers anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.71,0:10:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Best of all, a message can be\Ndelivered instantly... No more time lag.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.42,0:10:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For those magicians, did \Nit never come to mind
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.05,0:11:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that this was such an incredible discovery?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.87,0:11:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because of the difference\Nin perspective... They have no clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.26,0:11:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They only consider it a convenient device\Nto report their daily investigations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This sphere can also enable troops
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.11,0:11:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who are far apart to cooperate \Nwith one another...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.01,0:11:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such an idea never entered their minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.23,0:11:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Splendid! Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.65,0:11:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their views on the\N"Stone Walls" are no different.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olminu cast the charms to defend Toyohisa,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.85,0:11:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he used them a\Nlaunchpad instead, and now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.20,0:11:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...as a tool to breach the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.87,0:11:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the Drifters are those
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.62,0:11:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who introduce technology as well as\Nrecognize the differences in perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.43,0:11:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what on earth are \Nthese so-called "Ends"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.57,0:11:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of scheme do they have for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.06,0:11:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. That is what you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.52,0:11:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and what you are is the reason you are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.98,0:12:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That difference in view \Ncould change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stir it up, Drifters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.56,0:12:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no "way things \Nshould be" in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.41,0:12:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep the world turning, Drifters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The castle is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyo, let's go free the Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.22,0:12:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.23,0:12:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been told countless\Ntimes since childhood
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.14,0:12:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the Dwarves are strong warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.80,0:12:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Elves certainly despise the Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every night our fathers told us about them,\Nfilled with fear and loathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.86,0:12:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But behind all that lies a jealousy\Nfor the traits that the Elves lack.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.03,0:12:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their strength, their perseverance,\Ntheir sharp axes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.87,0:12:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are likely to be captives\Nhere in the castle town.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.77,0:13:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once, it was inconceivable for the Elves\Nto fight beside the Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.11,0:13:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.34,0:13:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the way things should have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.72,0:13:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get them out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.88,0:13:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Dwarves are vulgar, violent,\Nfoul barbarians with scruffy beards.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.68,0:13:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They drink a lot, eat a lot, smell bad,\Nand are totally frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.02,0:13:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their massive arms can\Ncrush boulders and strike steel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.40,0:13:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their massive legs stomp the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their massive axes cleave \Ntheir enemies in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.86,0:13:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And after all that, they go drinking,\Nlaughing and singing bawdily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.20,0:13:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the other buildings \Nare the same as this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place really is a concentration camp,\Na "workshop" in name only.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.13,0:13:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after we Elves surrendered,\Nthe Dwarves kept fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.18,0:13:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were lucky to have\Njust been made into serfs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.14,0:13:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the Dwarves were enslaved in\Nthe mines or in workshops all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.62,0:13:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were wondering about the\Ncommotion outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.85,0:14:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it your doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.98,0:14:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's ironic. You of all people\Ncame to save us, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.11,0:14:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"We" didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.70,0:14:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We too were saved... by the Drifters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.79,0:14:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever, doesn't matter. Free us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.33,0:14:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are through.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.21,0:14:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Free us. I'm begging you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.63,0:14:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please. Even if you are Elves...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...free us. We can fight as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.10,0:14:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:14:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you are Dwarves?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.56,0:14:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your beard is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.48,0:14:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really small. You're \Nalso really thin, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are... You are one of those "Drifters"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.07,0:14:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't care about that stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.57,0:14:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They just call me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.77,0:14:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An army marches on its stomach!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.83,0:14:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to eat! Time to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hum? What happened, Boobienu?\NWhat happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.09,0:15:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have the castle defenders fallen yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.80,0:15:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in! Boobienu!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.80,0:15:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... it appears Toyohisa\Nhas freed the Dwarves, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.06,0:15:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Dwarves were starving\Nand severely malnourished,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so Toyo started saying, "It's time to eat."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.52,0:15:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Don't tell me... they've begun eating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.36,0:15:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They haven't even taken over the keep yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.69,0:15:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They dug into the food storage,\Ncollected all the food in stock,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.78,0:15:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,including whatever survived the \Nfire, then dragged it over here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.20,0:15:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,mixed it all together in the \Npots, and started cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They actually started eating\Nin front of their enemies' eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.04,0:15:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh! The horses! The horses!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.64,0:15:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are butchering draft horses, warhorses,\Neverything, and starting to cook them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.92,0:15:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.47,0:15:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That jackass... really is an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.51,0:15:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa, I brought more raspberries for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.68,0:16:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm... this is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.10,0:16:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a reward, I shall present you with Gaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.36,0:16:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Make rice porridge!\N--Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to use plenty of water in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Food doesn't digest well after starvation,\Nwhich may lead to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.40,0:16:16.66,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"This is Monkey, my lord."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.86,0:16:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, that Monkey did a horrible thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.32,0:16:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said if you stuff yourself\Nquickly after starvation, you will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.66,0:16:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Monkey?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't allow those Dwarves to die on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh?!\N--Argh, annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.23,0:16:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell them to eat slowly!\NThat's all we can do for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.92,0:16:27.46,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nostalgic"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.46,0:16:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ranmaru! Bring me rice bowl soup also!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.88,0:16:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.76,0:16:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was aware of that, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.97,0:16:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aaaaahhh! I wanna eat rice!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.77,0:16:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.19,0:16:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is rice bowl soup?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The assault stopped?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.74,0:16:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that smoke?!\NWhat the hell are they doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.99,0:16:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.66,0:17:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have freed the Dwarves.\NThey're eating for now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.16,0:17:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you haven't run away by the\Ntime they are done, you will all die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.17,0:17:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you run, we won't chase after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.01,0:17:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drop your weapons and surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Decide quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.05,0:17:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Dwarves are focused on eating for now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.02,0:17:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there isn't much time\Nuntil they are through.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once the food runs out, you'll be next.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.31,0:17:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will completely devour you\Nall the way to your livers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.90,0:17:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's good. He is no fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.11,0:17:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything he knows, every skill he has,\Nis honed for the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.28,0:17:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the last bite!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.87,0:17:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, will you give up the keep\Nor will you die?! Decide!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.08,0:17:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.92,0:17:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What could we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They breached the first gate;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.75,0:17:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we don't have time to wait \Nfor reinforcements to arrive!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.59,0:17:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.34,0:18:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, the moment the Dwarves\Nfill their stomachs, they will come for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.85,0:18:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If those idiots dig through, we will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.89,0:18:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll kill us all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.36,0:18:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drifters! You're not going \Nto kill us, are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.32,0:18:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we give up the keep, \Nyou'll let us go, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.24,0:18:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the warrior's way of battle
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.32,0:18:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not to take the head of a soldier\Nwho lays down his arms!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm. They gave up gracefully. Next...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.34,0:18:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the lord of this castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.41,0:18:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.18,0:18:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already surrendered.\NYou'll let me go now, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.64,0:18:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I'll have them \Nset up a place for you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.47,0:18:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to commit ritual disembowelment,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so please wait for a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.48,0:18:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disembowelment?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.75,0:18:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall act as your second\Nand behead you at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.52,0:18:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you just say... disembowelment?!\NWhat the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.44,0:18:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lost the battle, therefore you lords
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.32,0:19:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must know that an honorable \Nsuicide should follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.21,0:19:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is your responsibility \Nand honor as a lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.54,0:19:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's absurd.\NDon't be an idiot, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.29,0:19:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the hell do I have to\Ncommit dis... disembowelment?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way in hell will I spill my own guts!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.05,0:19:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.46,0:19:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have what it takes to end yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.80,0:19:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are not fit to be lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing of value\Nyou possess is your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.65,0:19:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to pursue them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.77,0:19:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you knew, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.69,0:19:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you would assist me.\NYou're a man of your word.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.95,0:19:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just my old habit...\NThose were my previous orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.16,0:19:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody can order you to do anything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.16,0:19:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our battle to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.30,0:19:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's get back to the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.84,0:20:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoichi, are we going to pursue them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.60,0:20:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to do \Nthat... at least for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.73,0:20:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.78,0:20:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be able to get closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.87,0:20:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon cavalry are flying all over with\Ndetection charms hanging from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.53,0:20:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't use any of our charms or magic.\NThey will give us away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a difficult task.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.53,0:20:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only took this job because \Nit's for the Octobrists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.17,0:20:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had it been a normal assignment\Nfor the Adventurer's Guild,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.26,0:20:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have done it. It's too risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.30,0:20:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appreciate it, Doug.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.22,0:20:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.85,0:20:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is such a convenient telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.62,0:20:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that also a rumored \Nrelic of the Octobrists?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.10,0:20:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bronze Dragon! What the \Nhell?! It can't be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.94,0:21:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although he ranks last, he's still\None of the six Great Dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.82,0:21:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will he join the Black King's army?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.45,0:21:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the army stop advancing southward\Nbecause he joined the forces?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.78,0:21:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's probably not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.12,0:21:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at the southern \Ntip of the "Northern Wall."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.22,0:21:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps that's the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.33,0:21:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What on earth is that?!\NIs something wrong with my eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a field? Are those monsters farming?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.39,0:21:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster civilization?!\NThey've begun primitive agriculture!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.48,0:21:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are the Black King\Nand those idiots doing... over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.02,0:21:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...at the Northern Wall?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.94,0:21:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grand Master was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.93,0:21:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Black King is different \Nfrom the "Ends" we've known.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.90,0:21:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't wish the \Neradication of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.07,0:21:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His intention is to become a savior
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.74,0:21:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the monsters who would \Ntake the place of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.49,0:21:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.50,0:21:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.88,0:23:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Bedtime Stories"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.09,0:23:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Soup for Hundreds"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.67,0:23:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Cheaply Wasted"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.01,0:23:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Act 10\NBaba Yetu"
